{
  "texts": [
    "Consequently, techniques that facilitate automatic hyperparameter adjustment hold considerable promise.Lastly, we delve into three distinct groups of methods aimed at controlling the model's generalization tendencies.",
    "These encompass mechanisms for regulating the simplicity of learned solutions, fostering diversity among solutions, and introducing biases to steer the model's generalization trajectory in a desired direction.",
    "Role of the optimizerThe extent to which the choice of optimizer, often manifesting as a form of stochastic gradient descent (SGD), influences generalization performance prompts inquiry.",
    "Mingard et al. [79] provide insights by demonstrating that randomly sampling parameters as opposed to using SGD has negligible effects.",
    "Specifically, their study investigates the probability of a deep neural network trained with SGD converging to a specific input-output mapping on a given dataset."
  ]
}